DML_FDS_ADIRU1_CASVAL

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4051] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3384;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1072 1073:<1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.6>,<1.3.6.1>,<1.3.8>,<1.3.8.1>,<1.3.9>;
3383:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.4>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4.2>,<4.2.1>,<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.2>,<4.2.1.3>,<4.2.2>;
3384:<1>,<2>;
2535:<1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1072:<1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<3>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that the function performs the following:
1) If NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE or AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE, then the element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is reset and the element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set to FALSE. (<4.2>,<4.2.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) Failure is detected if the FS is not equal AIF_NORMALOPERATION. (<1>,<2>, of SDD_OPSW-CI-3384 , <1>,<4.2>,<4.2.1>,<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) If the failure condition is confirmed, then following elements of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set: (<1>,<2>, of SDD_OPSW-CI-3384 , <1>,<4.2>,<4.2.1>,<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.2>,<4.2.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3.1) FDSFailureValidated to TRUE
3.2) FailureConfItem to 0.
4) The FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set to FALSE and FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] are set to 0, if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4.1) FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE
4.2) AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE
4.3) AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE
5) If element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is FALSE,then the element NoRefrVL_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_NO_FAILURE_DETECTED (<1>,<1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)
6) If element AFDXCASFailFSNVM AND element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] are FALSE then the element FDS_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_NO_FAILURE_DETECTED (<1>,<1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)
7) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][0] is TRUE, then element FDS_ADIRU_CASVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to FALSE ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.6>,<1.3.6.1>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
8) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is TRUE, then element FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to FALSE ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.8>,<1.3.8.1>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
9) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][0] is FALSE and AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE, then element FDS_ADIRU_CASVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to FALSE ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.6>,<1.3.6.1>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
10) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is FALSE and AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE, then element FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to FALSE ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.8>,<1.3.8.1>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
11) Initialises AFDXConsolidatedCAS to 0. (<3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
12) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_FS for the messages ADIRU1(2,3) and the FDS1(2): (<1>,<1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
-Calls LIB_Initialise_Confirmation() for each FailureConfItem with 148 failure validation cycles
-FDSValid is set to FALSE for all Functional Data Sets
13) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_Message for the messages ADIRU1(2,3):(<1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- SignalName is set to ADI_ADIRU1(2,3)
- MsgHealingValidateConfItem is initialised to 101 by calling of LIB_Initialise_Confirmation() for all elements
- MsgFailureValidateConfItem is initialised to 148 by calling of LIB_Initialise_Confirmation() for all elements
- ExpectedPayLoadSize is set to 248 for all elements
- AFDXMessageFailureValidated and NewMsgReceived are set to FALSE for all elements
- A memory area is set to zero for every PayloadMsg. The reserved memory size is 248.
14) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_Output for messages ADIRU1(2,3):(<1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- RA_ADIRU_CAS is set to 0
- FDS_ADIRU_CASVal is set to FALSE
- FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal is set to FALSE
- MFPPitotHeat is set to FALSE
- ISPRightHeat is set to FALSE
- ISPLeftHeat is set to FALSE
- SSAHeat is set to FALSE
15) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is FALSE and AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE, then performs the following: (<2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
- Resets the element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] by calling LIB_Reset_Confirmation(). (<2.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
- Element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set to TRUE. (<2.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
- Element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set to FALSE. (<2.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test cases 1,2,5,7 and 10.
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test cases 1,2,5,7 and 10.
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 145 times before test case 3 to increment 'failure counter'.
4) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 143 times before test case 6 to increment 'failure counter'.
5) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 146 times before test cases 9, 12, 20 to increment 'failure counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:

2) Set the database entries as follows in test cases 2
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ACONGND].Data) = FALSE

3) Set the database entries as follows in test cases 5,7
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data) = TRUE

4) Set the database entries as follows in testcases 3,4,6,8,9
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data) = FALSE

5) Provide input as below in test case 17:
1..3=>StubReturn(AIF_AFDXGetMessage(AFDX_Message_11,x))

6) The following inputs are set to FALSE in test cases 1,2,5,7 and 10.
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A.Pre.Adiru1_Fds1_Failure_Validated)

Output Verification:
1) The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.
2) Expect the below output in test case 20:
ValueWritten2DB(Index,Value) = Index3 of MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4053
3) Expect the below output in test case 17:
ValueWritten2DB(Index,Value) = Index4

Note : The following outputs are verified in all the below MTS where ever the requirement is mapped.
1) The contents of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE is transmitted to the MSP via DPRAM is verified by calling FSE_Store_Failure_Event_DPRAM() for corresponding DPRAM indices (<3> of 2535 and <1>,<2> of 2536)
2) Monitor outputs to DB and outputs to NVM via DB are verified using DMA_Set() (<1>,<2> of 2538)
3) Post verification 1 and 2 of test case 12 and test cases 18 and 19 are same as test case 9 and 10 of MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4053 to verify that the FDSFailureValidated is set to TRUE (objective 3.1)
4) Post verification 3 and 4 of test case 12 are same as test case 11 and 12 of MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4051 to verify the FailureConfItem to 0 (objective 3.2) and Index3 of ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_17 is used for Post verification 3 of test case 12.
5) Test cases 15 and 16 are same as test cases 11 and 12 to verify the reset of the element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] and test cases 15 and 16 come after test case 1
6) Test case 20 is same as test case 3 to obtain the failure condition except Index,Value
7) Test case 21 is same as test case 4 which confirms the failure.
8) Test case 17 comes after test case 14 which is same as test case 2 except AFDX_Message and Index,Value. (Test Objective 15)
Coverage & Functional Issues:

The following part of requirement <1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072 cannot be verified:
AFDX_CASVal shall be set to FALSE
ADIRUAFDXCASFail shall be set to FALSE
The following part of requirement <3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072 cannot be verified:
AFDXConsolidatedCASVal to FALSE.
The requirement <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072 cannot be verified:
The array AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition shall be initialised for the messages ADIRU1(2,3)
CAS shall be set to FALSE
Status shall be set to FALSE
Message_Failure_Condition shall be set to FALSE
FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS shall be set to FALSE
FDS_Failure_Condition_Status shall be set to FALSE

The uncovered initialisations can not be covered by module test. This is justified, since its correct setting is ensured by code review

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_11














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4052] SDD_OPSW-CI-1073;SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-3384;SDD_OPSW-CI-1072 1073:<1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.4>,<1.3.5>,<1.3.5.4>,<1.3.8>,<1.3.8.1>,<1.3.9>;
3383:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<3>,<3.1>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
3384:<1>,<2>;
1072:<2>

Test Objective:
1) Read the value AFDX_Link_Failure and AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition from DB index DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE and DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION. (Behaviour 3383:<1>)

2) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is FALSE and AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE, then the following is performed: (Behaviour 3383:<2>)   
-Element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is set to TRUE. (Behaviour 3383:<2.1>)
-Element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is set to FALSE. (Behaviour 3383:<2.2>)   

3) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE or AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE and AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE and following is performed: (Behaviour 3383:<3>)
-Element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set to FALSE. (Behaviour 3383:<3.1>)

4) Healing is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (Behaviour 3383:<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>)
- FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is TRUE or AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE.
- AFDX_Link_Failure is FALSE
- element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE
- element NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE and AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE

5) If FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][0] is TRUE then following is performed. (Behaviour 1073:<1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.4>,<1.3.5>,<1.3.5.4>)
-element FDS_ADIRU_CASVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to TRUE

6) If FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is TRUE OR AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE and FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is FALSE , then following is performed: (Behaviour 1073: <1.3.8>,<1.3.8.1>, 3383:<3>,<3.1>)
6.1) FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to FALSE

7) Set the element AFDX_CASVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] to FALSE when following are satisfied: (Behaviour 1073: <1.3.9>)
- FDS_ADIRU_CASVal is TRUE
- FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal is FALSE

8) Returns FALSE, if the FS is equal to AIF_NORMALOPERATION. (Behaviour 3384:<1>,<2>)

9) Reads the following data from DPRAM FCP_A (access pointer DPR_Ptr_From_A using data structure Pre) and store them to FDSFailureValidated in AFDX_ADIRU_FS according the index and to AFDXCASFailFSNVM, AFDXCASFailUPNVM, AFDXCASFailDMNVM in AFDX_ADIRU_NVM according the index. (Behaviour 1072:<2>)

10) Resets the element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] by calling LIB_Reset_Confirmation(). (Behaviour 3383:<2.3>)

11) If healing is validated, then following elements of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] are set: (Behaviour 3383:<4.1.1.3>)
- FDSFailureValidated to FALSE
- FDSValid to TRUE

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Test Objectives:
1) The element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is reset if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383 )
1.1) The element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE
1.2) AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE or NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE
2) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is FALSE and AFDXMessageFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE, then the following is set: (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<2.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2.1) FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] to TRUE
2.2) FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] to FALSE
2.3) HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] to 0
3) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3.1) The element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE
3.2) The element NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE
3.3) AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE
4) If Healing condition is confirmed, then following elements of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is set: (4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4.1) FDSFailureValidated to FALSE
4.2) FDSValid to TRUE
4.3) HealingConfItem to 0
5) If element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][0] is TRUE then the function performs the following: ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.5>,<1.3.5.1>,<1.3.5.2>,<1.3.5.3>,<1.3.5.4>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
5.1) Get the CAS as the payload from message by calling AIF_GetFDSFromMsg()
5.2) Convert the payload from float to a scaled integer value by calling ICR_Float2IntIEEE754()
5.3) The converted payload is stored to element RA_ADIRU_CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i]
5.4) Element FDS_ADIRU_CASVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to TRUE
6) If element FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is TRUE then element FDS_ADIRU_StatusVal of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i] is set to TRUE. ( <1>,<1.1>,<1.2>,<1.3>,<1.3.1>,<1.3.2>,<1.3.3>,<1.3.7>,<1.3.9> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
7) If element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is FALSE,then the element NoRefrVL_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_NO_FAILURE_DETECTED (<1>,<1.1>,<3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)
8) If element AFDXCASFailFSNVM AND element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] are FALSE then the element FDS_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_NO_FAILURE_DETECTED (<1>,<1.2>,<3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)
9) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_FS for the messages ADIRU1(2,3) and the FDS1(2): (<1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
-Calls LIB_Initialise_Confirmation() for each HealingConfItem with 101 healing validation cycles and set heading counter to 0.

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_16 to 25”

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in testcases 1 ,2 , 8, 11 and 15
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in testcases 1 ,2 , 8, 11 and 15
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 98 times before test case 4 and 8 to increment 'healing counter'.
4) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 10, 14 and 18 to increment 'healing counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:

3) Post verification 3 and 4 of test case 18 are same as test case 17 and 18 of MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4053 to verify the HealingConfItem to 0 (objective 4.3).

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_25














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4054] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3385;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1072;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-3384 3383:<3>,<3.2>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1><4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3385:<1>,<2>,<3>,<4>,<5>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1072:<1.3>;
2535:<2>;
3384:<1>,<2>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies the following:
1) If element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE and DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE is TRUE, then reset healing counter. (Behaviour 3383:<3>,<3.2>)
2) If element NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE, AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE, and FS is not equal to AIF_NORMALOPERATION then confirm the validity using LIB_Confirm(),then perform the following: (Behaviour 3384:<1>,<2>), (Behaviour 3383:<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>)
-FDSFailureValidated to FALSE
-FDSValid to TRUE
3) FS (functional status) holds value PayloadMsg of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] from position 137 and set the element FunctionalStatus of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] accordingly. (Behaviour 3385:<1>)
4) Get the the heat status bits by calling the function AIF_GetFDSFromMsg() (Behaviour 3385:<2>)
5) Extract the heat status bits and save them to the following elements of AFDX_ADIRU_Output[i]: (Behaviour 3385:<3>)
-MFPPitotHeat: bit 4 of extracted payload
-ISPRightHeat: bit 6 of extracted payload
-ISPLeftHeat: bit 7 of extracted payload
-SSAHeat: bit 12 of extracted payload
6) A2 = TRUE if all the following conditions satisfies:(Behaviour 3385:<4>,<5>)
6.1) FS equals to AIF_NORMALOPERATION
6.2) Any of the following condition is satisfied:
6.2.1) MFPPitotHeat is set
6.2.2) ISPRightHeat is set
6.2.3) ISPLeftHeat is set
6.2.4) SSAHeat is set
7) A1 is TRUE if FS is not equal to AIF_NORMALOPERATION. (Behaviour 3385:<4>,<5>)
8) FunctionalStatus is set to AIF_NODATA for all Functional Data Sets. (Behaviour 1072:<1.3>)
9) Set the dependent engineering data DB entries as per the table "Dependent Engineering Data to DB" of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535 by using DMA_Set() and single bits and bit fields are assigned by using the functions BIT_Assign() and BIT_Assign_Field() respectively.(Behaviour 2535:<2>)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_26 and ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_27a to ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_27d”

Pre-condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) GloabalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data)=FALSE
3) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) 99 times before test case 3 to increment the healing counter

Input Stimulation:
1) In all the test cases except test case 1:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data)=FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION].Data) =FALSE

2) Test case 1:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data)=TRUE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION].Data) =TRUE

3) Test case 1:
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE

4) In all test cases provide inputs as follows:
1..3=>StubReturn(AIF_AFDXGetMessage(AFDX_Message,x))
AFDX_Message->SignalName = ADI_PFCS1
AFDX_Message->PayloadMsg = refer below tables

AFDX_Message->NewMsgReceived = TRUE
AFDX_Message->AFDXMessageFailureValidated = FALSE

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Output Verification:
1) StubCalled(AIF_AFDXGetMessage(x,TRUE)) in test case 1 and
StubCalled(AIF_AFDXGetMessage(x,FALSE)) in all test cases except test case 1 .
2) 1..6=>StubCalled(AIF_GetFDSFromMsg(152,x,x)) in all the test case except test case 1
3) The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.
4) Expect the following output in all test cases
1,3,5=>StubCalled(BIT_Assign_Field(x,0,7,x))
2,4,6=>StubCalled(BIT_Assign_Field(x,8,15,x))
5) Expect the following output in all test cases

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 of <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 )
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
4.2) Condition B1 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
5.2) The element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is reset
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6.2) Condition B is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<6>,<6.1>,<6.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
7.2) The element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_Discrepancy[1] is reset
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition B is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition B1 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[1].AFDX_CASVal is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
10) Condition B1 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[2].AFDX_CASVal is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
11) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- DM_FailureConfItem is initialised to 88 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
12) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- DM_HealingConfItem is initialised to 22 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_28 to 37” and ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Method_2

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 22 and 3 to increment 'healing counter'.
4) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 20 times before post verification 2 of test case 8 to increment 'healing counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 and <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
4.2) Condition B2 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
5.2) The element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is reset
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6.2) Condition B is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<6>,<6.1>,<6.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
7.2) The element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is reset
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition B is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition B2 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[1].AFDX_CASVal is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
10) Condition B2 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[2].AFDX_CASVal is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4058] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<6>,<6.1>,<6.2>,<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 and <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
4.2) Condition B3 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6.2) Condition B is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<6>,<6.1>,<6.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition B is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition B3 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[0].AFDX_CASVal and AFDX_ADIRU_Output[2].AFDX_CASVal are FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-4059] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;

2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 and <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
4.2) Condition B4 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6.2) Condition B is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<6>,<6.1>,<6.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition B is FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition B4 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[1].AFDX_CASVal and AFDX_ADIRU_Output[2].AFDX_CASVal are FALSE (<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Note: Refer SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 for conditions

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5611] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;

2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0, if AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE. (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 and <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
4.2) Condition C1 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6.2) Condition C is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<8>,<8.1>,<8.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition C is FALSE (<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Healing condition is not detected if Condition C4 is TRUE (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Note: Refer SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 for conditions

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5613] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;

2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0, if AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386 and <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
4.2) Condition C3 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
5.2) The element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is reset
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6.2) Condition C is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<8>,<8.1>,<8.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
7.2) The element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is reset
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition C is FALSE (<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition C3 is FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[0].AFDX_CASVal is TRUE (<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_98 to 106"

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 18 and 3 to increment 'healing counter'.
4) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 20 times before post verification 2 of test case 8 to increment 'healing counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:
1) Consider the below DML entries for all the test cases as mentioned in the default table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Default”

2) Provide input as below in test case 1:
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE

Output Verification:
1) The DML entries have been verified as per mentioned in the table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_100” and rest will be verified as specified in the default table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Default ” (refer MTS_OPSW-IVVP-4055)
2) The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.

Note:
1) Test case 16 is same as test case 1 and test case 17 is same as test case 2.
2) Post verification of test case 5 is same as test case 5 to verify the element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is reset (objective 5.2)
3) Post verification 1 and 2 of test case 8 are same as test case 6 and 8 to verify the element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_Discrepancy[2] is reset (objective 7.2).

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_106














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5614] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<8>,<8.1>,<8.2>,<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 when AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
4.2) Condition C4 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6.2) Condition C is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<8>,<8.1>,<8.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition C is FALSE (<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5615] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386,<1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A1 is TRUE.
5) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_135














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5619] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.2>,<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A1 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6.2) Condition A is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<4>,<4.1>,<4.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition A is FALSE (<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_136 to 144"

This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A2 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A3 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6.2) Condition A is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<4>,<4.1>,<4.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition A is FALSE (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Failure condition is not detected if Condition A is FALSE (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_152 to 158"

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_158














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5622] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<8>,<8.1>,<8.2>,<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<9>,<9.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
4.2) Condition C2 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is TRUE
6.2) Condition C is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<8>,<8.1>,<8.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[2] is FALSE
8) HealingConfItem is 0, if Condition C1 is TRUE (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) HealingConfItem is 0, if Condition C3 is TRUE (<8>,<8.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_159 to 164"

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 3 to increment 'healing counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:
1) Consider the below DML entries for all the test cases as mentioned in the default table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Default”

2) Provide input as below in test case 1:
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data) = TRUE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION].Data) = TRUE

3) Provide input as below in all test cases except 1:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ACONGND].Data) = TRUE

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<7>,<7.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
4.2) Condition B2 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is TRUE
6.2) Condition B is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<6>,<6.1>,<6.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[1] is FALSE
8) HealingConfItem is 0, if Condition B2 is TRUE (<6>,<6.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_165 to 169"

1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 3 to increment 'healing counter'.

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_169














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5624] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-3386;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>;
3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.2>,<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386, <1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A1 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6.2) Condition A is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<4>,<4.1>,<4.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
8) HealingConfItem is 0, if Condition A1 is TRUE (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) HealingConfItem is 0, if Condition A4 is TRUE (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_170 to 177"

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 3 and 12 to increment 'healing counter'.

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Input Stimulation:
1) Consider the below DML entries for all the test cases as mentioned in the default table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Default”

2) Provide input as below in test case 1:
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru1_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru2_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds1_Failure_Validated) = TRUE
GlobalData(ptu_ptr_DPR_Ptr_From_A->Pre.Adiru3_Fds2_Failure_Validated) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE].Data) = TRUE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION].Data) = TRUE

3) Provide input as below in all test cases except 1,10:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE

4) Refer “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Method_5” for methods and “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_90 “ for “AFDX_Message”

Output Verification:
1) The DML entries have been verified as per mentioned in the table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_170” and rest will be verified as specified in the default table “ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Default ” (refer MTS_OPSW-IVVP-4055)
2) The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.

Note: Test case 10 is same as test case 1 and test case 11 is same as test case 2

3386:<1>,<2>,<3>,<4>,<4.1>,<4.2>,<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>,<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>,<9>,<9.1>,<9.2>;
2535:<3>;

1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that function performs the following:
1) Initialize the FailureConfItem and HealingConfItem to 0 (<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
2) FDSValid set to FALSE if the validity of HealingConfItem is not confirmed. (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
3) FDSValid set to TRUE if the validity of HealingConfItem is confirmed (<4>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>, <4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3383)
4) Failure condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<3>,<5>,<5.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386,<1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073)
4.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
4.2) Condition A4 is TRUE.
5) If failure condition is confirmed, then (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
5.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
5.2) The element FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is reset
6) Healing condition is detected if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
6.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is TRUE
6.2) Condition A is FALSE
7) If healing condition is confirmed, then (<4>,<4.1>,<4.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
7.1) The element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is FALSE
7.2) The element HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0] is reset
8) FailureConfItem is 0, if Condition A is FALSE (<4>,<4.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)
9) Condition A, B, C are FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Output[0].AFDX_CASVal, AFDX_ADIRU_Output[1].AFDX_CASVal and AFDX_ADIRU_Output[2].AFDX_CASVal are FALSE. (<5>,<5.1>,<5.2>,<7>,<7.1>,<7.2>,<9>,<9.1>,<9.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3386)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_178 to 185" and ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_223

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test cases 1 and 17
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test cases 1 and 17
3) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 20 times before post verification 2 of test case 8 to increment 'healing counter'.
4) Call function AIM_ADIRU_Monitor 99 times before test case 3 and 15 to increment 'healing counter'.

[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5626] SDD_OPSW-CI-3383;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-2536;SDD_OPSW-CI-2538 3383:<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<3.3>,<4.1>,<4.1.1>,<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>,<4.1.1.3>,<4.1.2>,<4.2>,<4.2.1>,<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.2>,<4.2.1.3>,<4.2.2>;
2535:<3>;
2536:<1>,<2>;
2538:<1>,<2>

Test Objectives:
1) If AFDX_Link_Failure is TRUE and FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE then following is performed. (Behaviour 3383:<3>)
- FDSValid of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] =FALSE. (Behaviour 3383:<3.1>)
- HealingConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is reset by calling LIB_Reset_Confirmation. (Behaviour 3383:<3.2>)
- FailureConfItem of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is reset by calling LIB_Reset_Confirmation. (Behaviour 3383:<3.3>)
2) If AFDX_Link_Failure is FALSE and FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][j] is TRUE then following is performed. (Behaviour 3383:<4.1>)
2.1) If NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE and AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE then the following is performed. (Behaviour 3383:<4.1.1>)
2.1.1) determine the validity of healing condition (Behaviour 3383:<4.1.1.1>,<4.1.1.2>)
2.1.2) validate the the validity of healing condition by calling function LIB_Confirm. (Behaviour 3383:<4.1.1.1><4.1.1.3>)
2.2) If NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE or AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE then the healing is not confirmed. (Behaviour 3383:<4.1.2>)

3) If AFDX_Link_Failure is FALSE and FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[i][1] is FALSE, then failure validation is performed as follows (Behaviour 3383:<4.2>)
3.1) If NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is TRUE and AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE then the following is performed. (Behaviour 3383:<4.2.1>)
3.1.1) determine the validity of failure condition (Behaviour 3383:<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.2>)
3.1.2) validate the the validity of failure condition by calling function LIB_Confirm. (Behaviour 3383:<4.2.1.1>,<4.2.1.3>)
3.2) If NewMsgReceived of AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i] is FALSE or AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE then the failure is not confirmed. (Behaviour 3383:<4.2.2>)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer table
"ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_186 to 187"

2) 1..6=>StubCalled(AIF_GetFDSFromMsg(152,0,x)) in test cases 2,3,5,9,10,12,13,14,16,17,18, and 19
3) 1..3=>StubCalled(AIF_GetFDSFromMsg(152,0,x)) in test case 6.
4) The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_187














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5801] SDD_OPSW-CI-1072;SDD_OPSW-CI-3409;SDD_OPSW-CI-3408;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535 1072:<1.5>;
3409:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1>,<2.1.2>,<2.2>,<2.2.1>,<2.2.2>,<2.2.3>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.1.1>,<3.1.2>,<3.2>,<3.2.1>,<3.2.3>;
3408:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.2>,<4>,<5>,<6>,<7>,<8>;
2535:<1.1>,<1.2>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that the function performs the following:
1) Failure is detected, if the element CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
2) Failure is confirmed, if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.1>,<2.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
2.1) The element CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
2.2) The element FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
3) Failure is detected, if the element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
4) Failure is confirmed, if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.2><2.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
4.1) The element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
4.2) The element FDS_Failure_Condition_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
5) Healing is detected, if the condition A is TRUE and AFDXCASFailFSNVM in AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
6) If healing is confirmed, then the element AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is set to FALSE and confirmation counter is reset (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1>,<2.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
7) Healing is detected, if the condition A is TRUE and AFDXCASFailUPNVM in AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE is TRUE (<1>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
8) If healing is confirmed, then the element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is set to FALSE and confirmation counter is reset (<1>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.1.1>,<3.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
9) Failure is detected, if the element CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<3>,<3.2>,<3.2.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
10) Failure is confirmed, if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<1>,<3>,<3.2>,<3.2.1>,<3.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
10.1) The element CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
10.2) Message_Failure_Condition of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
11) Failure is detected, if the element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<3>,<3.2>,<3.2.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
12) Failure is confirmed, if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<1>,<3>,<3.2>,<3.2.1>,<3.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
12.1) The element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
12.2) Message_Failure_Condition of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
13) Set Message_Failure_Condition to FALSE and determine a CAS and Status FDS failure condition, if all the following conditions are satisfied: ( <1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3> SDD_OPSW-CI-3408 )
13.1) AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i].NewMsgReceived is TRUE
13.2) AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is FALSE
14) Set Message_Failure_Condition to TRUE and FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS and FDS_Failure_Condition_Status to FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i].NewMsgReceived is FALSE. ( <3>,<3.1>,<3.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
15) Set Message_Failure_Condition to TRUE and FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS and FDS_Failure_Condition_Status to FALSE, if AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i].NewMsgReceived and AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition are TRUE. ( <3>,<3.1>,<3.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
16) Set the following: (<6>,<7>,<8> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
16.1) Message_Failure_Condition to element Message_Failure_Condition of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i].
16.2) FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS to element FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i].
16.3) FDS_Failure_Condition_Status to element FDS_Failure_Condition_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i].
17) Determine a CAS inflight failure condition if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
17.1) Message_Failure_Condition,EngineActive are TRUE
17.2) ACOnGnd is FALSE
18) Determine a CAS inflight failure condition if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
18.1) FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS,EngineActive are TRUE
18.2) Message_Failure_Condition ,ACOnGnd are FALSE
19) Determine a Status inflight failure condition if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
19.1) Message_Failure_Condition,EngineActive are TRUE
19.2) ACOnGnd is FALSE
20) Determine a Status inflight failure condition if all the following conditions are satisfied:(<5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
20.1) FDS_Failure_Condition_Status,EngineActive are TRUE
20.2) Message_Failure_Condition,ACOnGnd are FALSE
21) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- FS_FailureConfItem_CAS is initialised to 498 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
22) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- FS_FailureConfItem_Status is initialised to 498 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
23) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- FS_HealingConfItem is initialised to 101 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
24) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- UP_HealingConfItem is initialised to 101 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
25) Initialises the array AFDX_ADIRU_NVM for the messages ADIRU1(2,3): (<1.5> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
- UP_FailureConfItem is initialised to 498 by calling LIB_Initialise_Confirmation()
26) Failure is not confirmed, when the element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE and FDS failure condition for Status given in element FDS_Failure_Condition_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is FALSE(<2.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
27) If element AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE then the element FDS_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_DETECTED_FAILURE. (<1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)
28) If element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE then the element NoRefrVL_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_DETECTED_FAILURE. (<1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)

Note: Refer SDD_OPSW-CI-3409 for conditions

1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test cases 1,5,9 and 13.

3) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 495 times before test case 17,19,21, and 23 to increment failure counter.
4) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 98 times before test cases 18,20,22, and 24 to increment healing counter.
5) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 200 times before test case 26 to increment failure counter.
6) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 295 times before test case 27 to increment failure counter.
7) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 496 times before test case 29 to increment failure counter.

Output Verification:

ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_199














...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5802] SDD_OPSW-CI-3409;SDD_OPSW-CI-3408 3409:<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.1>,<2.2.2>,<2.2.3>;
3408:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<4>

Test Objectives:
This MTS verifies that the function performs the following:
1) Failure is detected, if the element CAS of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
2) Failure is detected, if the element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
3) Failure is confirmed, if all the following conditions are satisfied: (<1>,<2>,<2.2>,<2.2.2>,<2.2.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
3.1) The element Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
3.2) The element FDS_Failure_Condition_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i] is TRUE
4) CAS inflight failure condition and Status inflight failure condition are not detected, if EngineActive is FALSE (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)
5) CAS inflight failure condition and Status inflight failure condition are not detected, if ACOnGnd is TRUE (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.2>,<2.3>,<4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3408)

Template Used: Coupling Standard Test Procedure

Coupling Table: Refer tables
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_200”
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_201”
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_202”
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_203”
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_204”
“ARE_AIM_ADIRU_Monitor_Test_205”

Pre-Condition/Setup:
1) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Initialise()) in test case 1.
2) CallOfFunction(DPR_Init()) in test case 1.
3) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 100 times before test case 2 and 4.
4) CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor()) for 496 times before test case 6.

Input Stimulation:
1) Set the database entries as follows in all test cases:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDXSTATUSFAIL].Data) = FALSE
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_AFDX_LINK_FAILURE_CONDITION.Data) = FALSE
2) Set the database entries as follows in the test cases:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ENGINEACTIVE].Data) = FALSE(in test cases 2)
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ENGINEACTIVE].Data) = TRUE(in test cases 1,3,4, 5 and 6)
3) Set the database entries as follows in the test cases:
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ACONGND].Data) = FALSE(in test cases 1,2,3,5 and 6)
GlobalData(DMA_Database[DML_ACONGND].Data) = TRUE(in test cases 4)

Transfer Action: CallOfFunction(AIM_ADIRU_Monitor())

Output Verification:
The outputs are verified by using standard output methods “ValueWritten2DB” and “StubCalled” as mentioned in the tables below.

...
[MTS_OPSW_P4-IVVP-5803] SDD_OPSW-CI-3409;SDD_OPSW-CI-3410;SDD_OPSW-CI-2535;SDD_OPSW-CI-1073 3409:<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1>,<2.1.2>;
3410:<1>,<1.1>;
2535:<1>,<1.2>;
1073:<1.4>

Test Objectives:
1) Healing is detected, if the element AFDXCASFailFSNVM in AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE and condition A is TRUE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409,<1.4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073, <1>,<1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3410)
2) If healing is confirmed, then the element AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is set to FALSE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1>,<2.1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
3) Healing is not detected, if AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i].FDS_Failure_Condition_Status is TRUE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
4) Healing is not detected, if AFDX_ADIRU_Inflight_Failure_Condition[i].FDS_Failure_Condition_CAS is TRUE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
5) Healing is not detected, if AFDX_ADIRU_Message[i].NewMsgReceived is FALSE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
6) Healing is not detected, if AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE. (<1>,<2>,<2.1>,<2.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
7) If element AFDXCASFailFSNVM is TRUE, then the element FDS_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_DETECTED_FAILURE. (<1>,<1.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)

6) Healing is not detected, if AFDX_Link_Failure_Condition is TRUE. (<1>,<3>,<3.1>,<3.1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-3409)
7) If element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[i] is TRUE then the element NoRefrVL_Failure_Status of AFDX_ADIRU_BITE[i] is set to FS_DETECTED_FAILURE (<1>,<1.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-2535)

Test Objectives:
1) Call the function DPX_Send_ARE_A_ADIRU_NVM_Latches. (<4> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1072)
2) If DPRAM(Access pointer DPR_Ptr_From_A using data structure x_20ms10ms) item Adiru1(2,3)AFDXCASFailFSNVM is equal to FALSE and element AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] is equal to TRUE, the function(<0>,<0.1> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073):
set element AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] to FALSE,
set element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[0(1,2)][0] to FALSE,
set element FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[0(1,2)][1] to FALSE,
set DB entry DML_ADIRU1(2,3)AFDXCASFAILFSNVM to FALSE using DMA_Set().
2.1>otherwise AFDXCASFailFSNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)], FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[0(1,2)][0] and FDSFailureValidated of AFDX_ADIRU_FS[0(1,2)][1] are same as initialized by DPRAM.
3) If DPRAM(Access pointer DPR_Ptr_From_A using data structure x_20ms10ms) item Adiru1(2,3)_AFDXCASFailUPNVM is equal to FALSE and element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] is equal to TRUE, the function (<0>,<0.2> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073):
set element AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] to FALSE,
set DB entry DML_ADIRU1(2,3)AFDXCASFAILUPNVM to FALSE using DMA_Set().
3.1> otherwise AFDXCASFailUPNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] is same as initialized by DPRAM.
4) If DPRAM(Access pointer DPR_Ptr_From_A using data structure x_20ms10ms) item Adiru1(2,3)_AFDXCASFailDMNVM is equal to FALSE and element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] is equal to TRUE, the function(<0>,<0.3> of SDD_OPSW-CI-1073):
set element AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] to FALSE,
set DB entry DML_ADIRU1(2,3)AFDXCASFAILDMNVM to FALSE using DMA_Set().
4.1> Otherwise AFDXCASFailDMNVM of AFDX_ADIRU_NVM[0(1,2)] is same as initialized by DPRAM.
